        "body": "### Problem\nThere is no Contributor's Guide in the repository, making it difficult for new contributors to understand the contribution process.\n\n### Proposed solution\n Create a Contributor's Guide that outlines contribution guidelines, code of conduct, and best practices.\n\n### Additional context\nA well-documented Contributor’s Guide is a best practice followed by many open-source and enterprise projects. It helps streamline the contribution process and improves project maintainability. Reference examples from established repositories (e.g., GitHub’s CONTRIBUTING.md templates) can be used as a starting point.\n\n### Part of\nThis issue aligns with the initiative to improve onboarding and collaboration efficiency within the project.\n",
